129
00:12:01,470 --> 00:12:04,330
Thank you for your hard work
for this period of time.

130
00:12:07,820 --> 00:12:10,760
The company has decided to give you

131
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:13,440
a final 2 weeks for observation.

132
00:12:14,290 --> 00:12:16,170
Up till midnight on June 6.

133
00:12:18,550 --> 00:12:19,850
The target KPI is

134
00:12:20,540 --> 00:12:23,050
sales of 10 billion KRW.

135
00:12:26,390 --> 00:12:28,070
If you don't hit

136
00:12:28,070 --> 00:12:30,990
the target sales within this time frame,

137
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:34,850
we'll follow our original plan
and disband Wonder-X.

138
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:38,660
10 billion KRW?

139
00:12:41,030 --> 00:12:43,330
We've just exceeded 5 billion KRW

140
00:12:43,950 --> 00:12:46,610
with all our sales
accumulated since our debut.

141
00:12:50,590 --> 00:12:51,350
This is

142
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:54,040
really the final chance.

143
00:12:57,880 --> 00:12:59,710
I believe you can do it.

144
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,600
We can do it.

145
00:13:10,220 --> 00:13:11,950
This was a difficult decision.

146
00:13:12,530 --> 00:13:14,880
Let me make this clear:

147
00:13:16,230 --> 00:13:17,880
popularity and buzz—

148
00:13:18,010 --> 00:13:20,010
they are both double-edged swords.

149
00:13:20,020 --> 00:13:21,530
Don't think you can get applause

150
00:13:21,530 --> 00:13:23,560
just by working hard.

151
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:25,250
What follows might be

152
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:27,170
more sharp criticism and condemnation—

153
00:13:27,170 --> 00:13:29,170
and even malicious attacks.

154
00:13:30,590 --> 00:13:32,280
Yebin and Minah are experienced,

155
00:13:32,280 --> 00:13:33,880
so they can get through it.

156
00:13:34,920 --> 00:13:37,250
But this target is different from before.

157
00:13:38,850 --> 00:13:39,980
Ji-eun especially—

158
00:13:40,670 --> 00:13:42,440
you need to be mentally prepared.

159
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:44,120
Determination is not enough.

160
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:45,890
You need a strong heart.

161
00:13:53,830 --> 00:13:54,630
All right.

162
00:13:55,410 --> 00:13:56,340
I'll stop here.

163
00:13:58,740 --> 00:14:01,240
Come on, tell me:

164
00:14:01,980 --> 00:14:02,960
how are you going

165
00:14:03,550 --> 00:14:04,820
to hit 10 billion KRW?

166
00:14:07,380 --> 00:14:08,740
A mini album.

167
00:14:09,470 --> 00:14:11,800
We will produce and release one
in 2 weeks.

168
00:14:12,820 --> 00:14:13,560
Two weeks?

169
00:14:15,470 --> 00:14:17,070
How is that possible?

170
00:14:19,710 --> 00:14:21,570
How can you say that's impossible

171
00:14:21,610 --> 00:14:23,210
before even trying?

172
00:14:25,570 --> 00:14:28,030
Ji-eun can compose,
I will write the lyrics,

173
00:14:28,590 --> 00:14:30,120
and Minah can be the visual.

174
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:38,020
We can reach 10 billion KRW...

175
00:14:39,580 --> 00:14:40,490
in 2 weeks.

176
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:21,900
[Evaluation Report]
[Rookie girl group Wonder-X's debut preparation and evaluation]

177
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:46,290
This won't work.

178
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:50,340
This melody is too ordinary.

179
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:53,840
Shall we take a break?

180
00:15:55,920 --> 00:15:56,640
Bin.

181
00:15:57,390 --> 00:15:59,120
We don't have time to rest.

182
00:16:11,030 --> 00:16:12,230
Shall I play for you?

183
00:16:14,160 --> 00:16:14,550
Huh?

184
00:16:52,250 --> 00:16:53,020
This is...

185
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:04,640
The song you wrote for me
in our high school freshman year—

186
00:17:05,380 --> 00:17:06,310
do you remember?

187
00:17:08,310 --> 00:17:09,319
The title...

188
00:17:09,940 --> 00:17:11,210
Was it "Scandal Love"?

189
00:17:15,250 --> 00:17:16,290
I was serious

190
00:17:16,970 --> 00:17:18,470
back then, though.

191
00:17:25,450 --> 00:17:26,310
I remember now.

192
00:17:36,070 --> 00:17:37,500
I'm exhausted.

193
00:17:40,270 --> 00:17:42,300
The school club is too tiring.

194
00:17:44,250 --> 00:17:45,890
Should I just quit?

195
00:17:58,280 --> 00:18:00,150
Why did you bring your guitar?

196
00:18:03,860 --> 00:18:04,490
Bin.

197
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:05,280
Yeah?

198
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:08,510
I wrote a song.

199
00:18:10,660 --> 00:18:11,330
Really?

200
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:12,120
You?

201
00:18:12,920 --> 00:18:14,340
Can you play it for me?

202
00:18:14,630 --> 00:18:15,490
Quick!

203
00:18:18,300 --> 00:18:20,480
The song is called

204
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:21,930
"Scandal Love."

205
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:25,250
It's not that it's a great song.

206
00:18:25,950 --> 00:18:27,610
Don't laugh after hearing it.

207
00:18:27,770 --> 00:18:29,310
Why would I laugh at you?

208
00:18:29,420 --> 00:18:30,620
Play it for me, quick!

209
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:38,990
Ji-eun.

210
00:19:40,730 --> 00:19:42,360
Is the "Love" in this song

211
00:19:42,960 --> 00:19:44,730
me?

212
00:19:48,350 --> 00:19:48,860
Yeah.

213
00:19:50,170 --> 00:19:51,700
Ji-eun, listen carefully.

214
00:19:52,300 --> 00:19:53,830
You’re my future composer—

215
00:19:54,520 --> 00:19:55,850
my exclusive producer.

216
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,670
We will reach the top.

217
00:20:00,370 --> 00:20:02,030
So we won't give up.

218
00:20:02,810 --> 00:20:03,540
Understand?

219
00:21:13,170 --> 00:21:14,600
I think the chorus

220
00:21:14,930 --> 00:21:16,590
can be repeated another time.

221
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:20,730
Okay.

222
00:21:21,330 --> 00:21:23,960
Let me think about the lyrics.

223
00:22:32,550 --> 00:22:33,400
Use this.

224
00:22:34,930 --> 00:22:37,030
Are you fighting a pencil?

225
00:22:39,930 --> 00:22:40,710
Thank you,

226
00:22:40,710 --> 00:22:41,170
Jin.

227
00:22:42,380 --> 00:22:45,840
Normally, I'd fight my pencil
if I can't solve some equations.

228
00:22:48,940 --> 00:22:49,740
That's right.

229
00:22:50,770 --> 00:22:52,100
I've seen that.

230
00:22:57,020 --> 00:22:57,950
Does that mean

231
00:22:58,860 --> 00:23:01,160
you've been watching me do my homework?

232
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:03,990
Yes.

233
00:23:06,230 --> 00:23:08,430
You look like the heroine of a comic book

234
00:23:09,270 --> 00:23:11,340
when you're studying hard.

235
00:23:13,740 --> 00:23:14,870
What are you talking about?

236
00:23:14,870 --> 00:23:16,270
What comic protagonist?

237
00:23:17,520 --> 00:23:18,820
Are you pulling my leg?

238
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:25,640
Yes.

239
00:23:26,510 --> 00:23:29,230
Let the pencil off
next time you get it wrong.

240
00:23:33,690 --> 00:23:34,750
So

241
00:23:35,250 --> 00:23:37,120
you always look at me when I study?

242
00:23:41,030 --> 00:23:41,700
Yes.

243
00:23:42,840 --> 00:23:44,830
You look like the heroine of a comic book

244
00:23:44,830 --> 00:23:46,920
when you're studying hard.

245
00:23:49,890 --> 00:23:51,430
What are you talking about?

246
00:23:52,330 --> 00:23:53,590
Are you pulling my leg?

247
00:23:57,460 --> 00:23:58,230
But

248
00:23:58,930 --> 00:24:01,730
the comic protagonist
needs some encouragement.

249
00:24:02,490 --> 00:24:03,420
Ms. Ji-eun,

250
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:06,560
can you teach me
how to solve this question?

251
00:24:10,350 --> 00:24:10,980
Sure.

252
00:24:13,260 --> 00:24:15,060
I'll teach you once.

253
00:24:35,930 --> 00:24:37,030
Teach me.

254
00:24:39,150 --> 00:24:39,950
Quick!

255
00:25:21,550 --> 00:25:22,450
Wonder-X...

256
00:25:24,150 --> 00:25:25,160
Wonder-X...
